WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:12.000
What was it like for you guys, especially after you lose Dylan and now you're down two big ball handlers with him and Fox, what was the challenge like there and how do you think you guys handled it?

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:22.000
No, well, we got to help our ball handlers more and take care of the ball.

00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:34.000
Obviously, without Darren, it's going to lend itself to turnover issues, but are there other factors that you guys can shore up to try to cut down on?

00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:44.000
Yeah, of course, just consistency throughout the game in our game plan. I can think of a few down moments for myself, especially in the fourth quarter.

00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:55.000
Victor, you and Harnstein had some huge battles on the glass there. He was able to win a lot of those, but what was that battle like for you and what do you think you guys can do better to not lose that way?

00:00:56.000 --> 00:01:11.000
As I just said, it's all in the scouting. I have to trust the scouting. We have to trust it and do our work early. It's a straight effort.

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:18.000
Victor, what would you say is the most frustrating thing about tonight's loss?

00:01:19.000 --> 00:01:29.000
I would say it's spending so much energy on catching back up to the score and then let it go away.

00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:36.000
When you say it's straight effort, is it that simple or are there some tactical, strategic kind of adjustments you can make?

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:47.000
What I mean is straight effort is the tactics, we all know it by heart, but it doesn't mean it's easy and we have to work through it.

00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:52.000
What did you think of Steph's performance tonight and the way that he played through physicality?

00:01:53.000 --> 00:02:05.000
His competitiveness is unmatched. We definitely need it. He gets us out of a lot of tough situations.

00:02:06.000 --> 00:02:17.000
Deirin is the one that controls the offense and settles you guys down a lot of the time. You don't have him, you don't have Dylan. What do you try to do to keep things organized, controlled and settled down?

00:02:17.000 --> 00:02:31.000
We didn't do a great job at it today, but we need some points for sure, taking care of the ball, helping the main ball handlers and being aggressive just like we were in the third quarter.

00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:36.000
Victor, when it comes to carding Shea, obviously you guys did a really good job of that in game one.

00:02:37.000 --> 00:02:45.000
More points tonight, is there any kind of balance there between wanting to keep his numbers down and understanding that he's a good player and he's going to make shots regardless of what you guys are doing?

00:02:45.000 --> 00:02:58.000
Yeah, he makes shots but nothing that he hasn't made all season so we worked on it and we just didn't apply as much.

00:02:58.000 --> 00:03:17.000
Victor, I have an impression tonight. A big advantage they have is the depth of the bench. I look at the numbers tonight. 57 points in a row apart from their bench.

00:03:17.000 --> 00:03:26.000
How do they do that? At that moment, they take fire like that, where they can always have a guy who's able to score.

00:03:30.000 --> 00:03:42.000
We need consistency. The depth of the bench is one of our strengths. We can't play fast, but we can't play fast if we don't defend, if we lose the ball.

00:03:42.000 --> 00:03:51.000
It's them who take advantage of that and it's a common strength for other teams but it's them who have had the advantage on that field today.

00:03:52.000 --> 00:03:57.000
Hartenstein defended very physically on you tonight, sometimes even at the limit of the rules.

00:03:58.000 --> 00:04:04.000
How do you stay focused to stay in the game, not to get out of it for a second? How as a team and you personally, do you manage to deal with that?

00:04:04.000 --> 00:04:19.000
We need to learn from all this energy. It's not different from the 13 games of the playoffs. It's not different from the 12 first games.

